// A zero-width slice (`x[4..4]`, width 0) is total, not an error: it routes
// through the prelude `Slice` guard whose `const if w == 0` emits the
// effective-0-bit value (`'0` into a `[-1:0]` net) rather than an illegal
// reversed/empty part-select (planning/slice_guards.md). Generic code that folds
// a width to 0 at its limit thus needs no `n == 0` special case.
fn empty(x: bits(8)) -> bits(0) {
    x[4..4]
}
